premise_source_doc_sentence: By the end of the century , Romanticism initiated a surge of enthusiasm for all things Greek , including Greek mythology .

In England , Chaucer , the Elizabethans and John Milton were among those influenced by Greek myths ; nearly all the major English poets from Shakespeare to Robert Bridges turned for inspiration to Greek mythology .
Greek mythology is explicitly embodied in a large collection of narratives , and implicitly in Greek representational arts , such as vase-paintings and votive gifts .
In northern Europe , Greek mythology never took the same hold of the visual arts , but its effect was very obvious on literature .

With the rediscovery of classical antiquity in the Renaissance , the poetry of Ovid became a major influence on the imagination of poets and artists , and remained a fundamental influence on the diffusion and perception of Greek mythology through subsequent centuries .
